## 🐛 Bug Report

<!-- A clear and concise description of what the bug is. -->

Lib version: 4.3.0

## Steps To Reproduce

<!-- The exact steps required to reproduce the issue, ideally with a code example -->

```javascript
const ExcelJS = require('exceljs')

let workbook1 = new ExcelJS.stream.xlsx.WorkbookWriter({
    filename: './speedTest.xlsx'
});
let sheet = workbook1.addWorksheet('My Sheet');
let sheet2 = workbook1.addWorksheet('My Sheet2');

console.log('begin')
console.time('write to excel time')
const rowData = ['Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1Test 1', 1]

for (let i = 0; i < 500000; i++) {
    sheet.addRow(rowData).commit();
    sheet2.addRow(rowData).commit();
}
sheet.commit();
sheet2.commit();

workbook1.commit()
console.timeEnd('write to excel time')
```

